news.title: Pinterest to reduce office spaces as part of restructuring
news.para: US companies from technology to finance have stepped up cost cuts as they brace for a potential recession. Pinterest said it expected to incur between $100 million and $125 million in charges related to the restructuring plan.

news.title: Maharashtra: Homebuyers can access all project details with QR code
news.para: ​The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) has started assigning QR codes to the registration certificates of developers across the state.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's air pollution control plan rests on builder self-certification
news.para: Civic action will follow if builders fail to self-certify that a construction site meets dust mitigation guidelines like erecting metal sheets around the periphery of construction sites, water-fogging during excavation and loading/unloading construction material and sprinkling of soil strata from time to time before excavation starts.

news.title: Haryana-RERA resolved only 50% plaints in five years; buyers say 'too slow'
news.para: Homebuyers have claimed that resolution of complaints before HRera was too slow, forcing many to approach other authorities for justice.

news.title: Can't force buyer to take late flat possession: Punjab RERA
news.para: Ajay Pal Singh, member, Rera, while giving relief to Panchkula residents Niklesh Dubey and Anuja Dubey, directed "Sushma Chandigarh Grande" housing society in Zirakpur to refund the flat booking amount along with interest in addition to harassment charges.

news.title: Sunac China reaches restructuring deal with offshore creditor group
news.para: Sunac, one of the biggest property developers in China, is among the many that defaulted last year as the sector reeled under a debt crisis.

news.title: Chennai: Property tax keeps the cash flowing
news.para: While the corporation projected a deficit of `788.5 crore for financial year 2022-23, the actual deficit fell further to 517.6 crore.

news.title: Regularisation law not weapon to be utilized for illegal construction: Bombay HC
news.para: The HC declined to entertain a plea by a hotelier who sought orders to restrain a civic body from demolishing the illegal structures and enable making an application for regularisation.

news.title: Bill tabled to enable home owners form association in Odisha
news.para: Under the Odisha Apartment Ownership Bill 2023, which will replace Orissa Apartment Ownership Act 1982, common areas such as corridors, staircases, lifts, play area and entire land of apartments will be registered in the name of the buyers' associations.

news.title: Adani Group seeks more time to pay ACC, Ambuja debt
news.para: According to the sources cited, the group has begun negotiations with lenders to extend the tenor of its $3 billion bridge from the existing 18 months to a period of five years or beyond.

news.title: Guideline value hiked to bridge gap with market value: Tamil Nadu minister
news.para: Moorthy said the guideline values were far below the market values in major cities like Chennai, Coimbatore and Madurai, owing to which government and private sector employees found it difficult to raise bank loans to buy properties.

news.title: Sagar Cements to furnish corporate guarantee of Rs 665 crore to SBI for loan availed by Andhra Cement
news.para: "Our board has also approved a proposal to pledge 25% of Sagar Cement's holdings in Andhra Cements in favour of the said banker as further security for the said loan," it said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Housing plot sales surge in Rajasthan; double stamp duty hits flats
news.para: While the natural preference to own one’s roof is a compelling reason, the stamp duty structure has also been major reason behind the spike. But developers feel rampant plotting could contribute to chaotic growth of city.

news.title: Embassy REIT acquires Embassy Business Hub for Rs 3,348 million in Bengaluru
news.para: Embassy REIT will acquire the entire paid up share capital of ECPL from the sellers, i.e., JV Holding (JVHPL, an affiliate of Embassy Property Developments) and another shareholder of the Embassy group.

news.title: Haryana CM tells officials to create separate dashboard for all properties of HSVP
news.para: The chief minister, who is also the chairman of HSPV, was presiding over the 125th meeting of the authority here, according to an official statement.
